article.headline: Humphrey has 25 points, 11 rebounds
article.linkText: Humphrey does double duty in Georgia win
article.story:
DULUTH, Ga. (AP) -- Tasha Humphrey scored 25 points, and Cori
Chambers added 22 to lead No. 18 Georgia to an 88-60 win over
Clemson on Sunday.

Humphrey, a freshman, also had 11 rebounds for her 11th
double-double of the season, tops in the Southeastern Conference.

Georgia improved to 20-6, marking the 21st time in 26 seasons
that coach Andy Landers' teams have reached 20 victories. Landers'
teams are 358-5 when scoring at least 81 points.

Clemson (7-16) lost its 10th straight game, the previous nine
coming against Atlantic Coast Conference opponents.

Sherill Baker had a season-best seven steals for Georgia.

The Lady Bulldogs improved to 11-5 against Clemson, including
3-0 at neutral sites. Arkansas beat Georgia Tech 71-59 in the first
game of the SEC-ACC doubleheader.

Reggie Maddox led Clemson with 18 points.

The Tigers pulled within 13 at the 5:54 mark when Maxienne White
hit an 8-foot runner off the glass.

Chambers answered with consecutive 3-pointers from the left side
before Humphrey hit a pair of free throws to make it 78-57 with
4:20 remaining.
